criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients known with symptomatic carotid artery stenosis (≥2 mm carotid plaque on
             duplex ultrasound), who are scheduled in the clinical setting to undergo a carotid
             endarterectomy or who are referred to conservative therapy;

          -  Age 18 years and older (no maximum age);

          -  Informed consent by signing informed consent form regarding this study.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Dementia, pregnancy, nursing mothers;

          -  Serious neurological deficits at symptomatic side (hemi paralysis, complete aphasia);

          -  Severe heart failure NYHA III-IV and severe pulmonary dysfunction dependent on oxygen
             supply;

          -  Patients with contra-indications for MRI (ferromagnetic implants like pacemakers or
             other electronic implants, metallic splinters in the eyes, vascular clips,
             claustrophobia, etc.).
